  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6820.29 sitting just above the GEX flip at 6795 and below the massive +102.5B gamma wall at 6830, dealers are in active selling mode as they hedge long gamma positions. The PIN regime and dense positive gamma walls from 6810-6840 create a strong magnetic pull toward mean reversion, with dealers providing natural resistance on any push toward 6830 and support if we test back toward the flip level. Watch for dealer buying to intensify if we break below 6795, while the 6830 wall represents significant technical resistance where dealer selling pressure peaks.\n\n**Bottom line:** expect price to get pinned between 6795-6830 with choppy, range-bound action.",
